#: ../../user-manual/preservation/preservation-planning.rst:489
msgid "Characterization"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user-manual/preservation/preservation-planning.rst:491
msgid ""
"Characterization is the process of producing technical metadata for an "
"object. Archivematica's characterization aims both to document the "
"object's significant properties and to extract technical metadata "
"contained within the object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user-manual/preservation/preservation-planning.rst:496
msgid "Characterization tools"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user-manual/preservation/preservation-planning.rst:498
msgid ""
"Archivematica has four characterization tools available upon "
"installation. Which tool will run on a given file depends on the type of "
"file, as determined by the identification tool."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user-manual/preservation/preservation-planning.rst:502
msgid ""
"The default characterization tool is FITS; it will be used if no specific"
" characterization rule exists for the file being scanned. It is possible "
"to create new default characterization commands, which can either replace"
" FITS or run alongside it on every file."
